<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[189,1398,267,478]" box="[189,406,267,293]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,406,267,293]" fontSize="11" level="4" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" reason="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,406,267,293]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Short description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[189,1398,267,478]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Epiphytic; long-creeping filiform rhizomes, rootless and densely covered by dense black trichomes, bearing widely separated pending fronds; fronds subsessile or with short stipes, up to 5 cm long, oblong to ovate, lobed to pinnatifid, with palmate to pinnate venation and false veins parallel to true veins, hairy with dark not pedunculated trichomes on lamina margins; sori few, epitactic, cylindrical with lips usually parallel and with brown margins.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
