</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[189,1399,895,1478]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
African 
<taxonomicName box="[288,607,895,921]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="robinsonii">
<emphasis box="[288,607,895,921]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Didymoglossum robinsonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically quite close to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Sw.) C. Presl" authorityName="(Sw.) C.Presl" box="[1020,1313,895,921]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reptans">
<emphasis box="[1020,1145,896,921]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">D. reptans</emphasis>
(Sw.) C.Presl
</taxonomicName>
and as such was considered a synonym of the latter species (
<bibRefCitation author="Wessels Boer J. G." box="[847,1083,930,957]" journalOrPublisher="Acta Botanica Neerlandica" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="277 - 330" part="11" refString="Wessels Boer J. G. 1962. The new world species of Trichomanes sect. Didymoglossum and Microgonium. Acta Botanica Neerlandica 11: 277 - 330." title="The new world species of Trichomanes sect. Didymoglossum and Microgonium" type="journal article" year="1962">Wessels Boer 1962</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Roux J. P." box="[1099,1237,930,957]" journalOrPublisher="Strelitzia" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" part="23" refString="Roux J. P. 2009. Synopsis of the Lycopodiophyta and Pteridophyta of Africa, Madagascar and neighbouring islands. Strelitzia 23." title="Synopsis of the Lycopodiophyta and Pteridophyta of Africa, Madagascar and neighbouring islands" type="journal volume" year="2009">Roux 2009</bibRefCitation>
). In addition, paleotropical 
<taxonomicName box="[349,472,966,991]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reptans">
<emphasis box="[349,472,966,991]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">D. reptans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has often been identified as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hook.) J. P. Roux" authorityName="(Hook.) J.P.Roux" box="[806,1178,965,992]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montanum">
<emphasis box="[806,966,966,991]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">D. montanum</emphasis>
(Hook.) J.P.Roux
</taxonomicName>
, especially by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sim T. R." journalOrPublisher="The University Press, Cambridge" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Sim T. R. 1915. The ferns of South Africa. The University Press, Cambridge." title="The ferns of South Africa" type="book" year="1915">Sim (1915)</bibRefCitation>
or 
<bibRefCitation author="Tardieu-Blot M. - L." box="[307,546,999,1026]" editor="Humbert H." journalOrPublisher="famille" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="16 - 38" part="3" refString="Tardieu-Blot M. - L. 1951. Hymenophyllacees. In: Humbert H. (ed.) Flore de Madagascar et des Comores, famille 3: 16 - 38. MNHN, Paris." title="Hymenophyllacees" type="journal article" volumeTitle="Flore de Madagascar et des Comores" year="1951">Tardieu-Blot (1951)</bibRefCitation>
. Types of 
<taxonomicName box="[667,790,1000,1025]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reptans">
<emphasis box="[667,790,1000,1025]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">D. reptans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[848,1008,1000,1025]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montanum">
<emphasis box="[848,1008,1000,1025]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">D. montanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are both neotropical, and exhibit identical diagnostic characters, explaining why we consider that these two taxa are synonyms (
<taxonomicName box="[1278,1399,1035,1060]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reptans">
<emphasis box="[1278,1399,1035,1060]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">D. reptans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has priority) as previously considered by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wessels Boer J. G." box="[676,924,1069,1096]" journalOrPublisher="Acta Botanica Neerlandica" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="277 - 330" part="11" refString="Wessels Boer J. G. 1962. The new world species of Trichomanes sect. Didymoglossum and Microgonium. Acta Botanica Neerlandica 11: 277 - 330." title="The new world species of Trichomanes sect. Didymoglossum and Microgonium" type="journal article" year="1962">Wessels Boer (1962)</bibRefCitation>
. By considering such synonymy and the 
<emphasis box="[189,280,1105,1130]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">a priori</emphasis>
of paleotropical 
<taxonomicName box="[483,606,1105,1130]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reptans">
<emphasis box="[483,606,1105,1130]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">D. reptans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
populations, 
<taxonomicName box="[767,891,1105,1130]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reptans">
<emphasis box="[767,891,1105,1130]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">D. reptans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would be present in Neotropics, in eastern and southern Africa and in the western Indian Ocean, but would be absent in western and central Africa (according to collections and 
<bibRefCitation author="Roux J. P." box="[548,686,1174,1200]" journalOrPublisher="Strelitzia" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" part="23" refString="Roux J. P. 2009. Synopsis of the Lycopodiophyta and Pteridophyta of Africa, Madagascar and neighbouring islands. Strelitzia 23." title="Synopsis of the Lycopodiophyta and Pteridophyta of Africa, Madagascar and neighbouring islands" type="journal volume" year="2009">Roux 2009</bibRefCitation>
). However, unpublished personal molecular data (based on 
<emphasis box="[189,228,1208,1234]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">rbc</emphasis>
L sequences) would indicate that neotropical 
<taxonomicName box="[764,888,1209,1234]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reptans">
<emphasis box="[764,888,1209,1234]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">D. reptans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would be genetically close and yet distinct from paleotropical specimens from Madagascar and Comoros (i.e., they do not form a monophyletic cluster). The disjunct distribution and the genetic differences thus suggest that Comorian supposed 
<taxonomicName box="[189,315,1313,1338]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reptans">
<emphasis box="[189,315,1313,1338]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">D. reptans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(often identified as 
<taxonomicName box="[565,728,1313,1338]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montanum">
<emphasis box="[565,728,1313,1338]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">D. montanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) could be a distinct species and thus likely considered 
<taxonomicName box="[189,347,1347,1373]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="robinsonii">
<emphasis box="[189,347,1347,1373]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">D. robinsonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(type from South Africa) as a distinct (potentially cryptic) taxon and not a synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[189,312,1383,1408]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reptans">
<emphasis box="[189,312,1383,1408]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">D. reptans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Additional molecular phylogenetic investigations including African specimens are required to clarify the taxonomic status of the paleotropical populations. Pending such revision we name the Comorian species 
<taxonomicName box="[406,562,1452,1478]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="robinsonii">
<emphasis box="[406,562,1452,1478]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">D. robinsonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
